Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the rigatoni.

When boiling, add the @dried rigatoni{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{10-12%mins}. Once cooked, reserve 100ml pasta water (per 2P) for the sauce.

Drain the pasta in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot, off the heat.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest and quarter the @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Chop the @smoked salmon{100%g} into 1cm pieces.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw salmon.

When the pasta is almost ready, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Fry the garlic until fragrant, ~{30%secs}. Add the @cream cheese{48%g}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet}, reserved pasta water, ½ tsp lemon zest (per 2P) and @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice).

Simmer for ~{2-3%mins} then add the pasta, salmon and @baby spinach{120%g}.

Allow the spinach to wilt and season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and lemon juice.

Divide the salmon pasta between #plates{}.

Sprinkle the @Italian style hard cheese{1%unit}(grated) over the top.

Serve the remaining lemon wedges alongside.